%N A396882 a(n) is the number of distinct triples of triangles chosen from n^2 unit triangles of a triangular grid up to rotation and reflection such that all three triangles lie in the same row parallel to a side of the grid.
%C A396882 Oblique coordinate system is defined taking X axis and Y axis along two edges of the triangular grid of unit triangles n^2. Side length of a unit triangle is taken as 3 units to obtain integer coordinates for the centroids of all unit triangles. Each triangle in the grid is uniquely denoted by coordinates of its centroid.
%C A396882 Triangles in a triplet are in a same row parallel to a side of the triangular grid if centers of the three triangles in a triplet lie in one of the two lines or two in one line and the remaining in the second line described below:
%C A396882 Parallel to AB: y = k or y = k + 1, where 1 <= k < 3n-2,
%C A396882 Parallel to AC: x = h or x = h + 1, where 1 <= h < 3n-2,
%C A396882 Parallel to BC: x + y = r or x + y = r + 1, where 1 < r <= 3n-2.
%C A396882 Any set of triplets fully obtainable by one of the following transformations produce reflections and are considered as duplicates: (h,k) into (n-h-k,h), (h,k) into (k,h), (h,k) into (h,n-h-k).
%H A396882 Janaka Rodrigo, <a href="/A396882/a396882.txt">Python Code for A396882</a>
%F A396882 a(n) = A396761(n) - A006325(n). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jun 16 2026
%e A396882 n = 3 has 3 sets of triplets of triangles which can be obtained by removing the following 7 sets from A396761(3): {(1,1), (1,4), (1,7)}, {(1,1), (1,4), (2,2)}, {(1,1), (1,4), (2,5)}, {(1,1), (1,7), (2,2)}, {(1,1), (2,2), (2,5)}, {(1,4), (2,2), (2,5)}, {(1,4), (2,2), (4,1)}.
%e A396882 Therefore a(3) = 13.
%Y A396882 Cf. A006325, A396285, A396761, A396762.
